com.bigdata.rdf.internal

Class InlineURIHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.bigdata.rdf.internal.InlineURIHandler
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    InlineHexUUIDURIHandler, InlineIPv4URIHandler, InlineNamespaceMultiURIHandler, InlineSignedIntegerURIHandler, InlineUnsignedIntegerURIHandler, InlineUUIDURIHandler, MultipurposeIDHandler, TestInlineURIs.MultipurposeInlineIDHandler

    public abstract class InlineURIHandler
extends Object
    Handler is mapped to a namespace prefix. When a URI is presented that matches the handler's namespace prefix, this class attempts to parse the remaining portion of the URI into an inline literal. The namespace prefix must be present in the vocabulary. The localName must be parseable into an inline literal. If either of these things is not true the URI will not be inlined.
